  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether rapid eye movements called saccades are
      impaired in glaucoma, a neurodegenerative disease of visual pathways.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Eye movements that quickly scan a visual scene are critical to a number of daily activities
      including driving. It is not known whether rapid eye movement called saccades, are altered in
      glaucoma.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
